Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.25,0:00:06.25,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1250,6250}FABLES \N of the\NGREEN FOREST
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.48,0:00:06.25,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:4480,6250}{\i1\c&HFFFFFF&}Today's episode:\N{\c&H25CE1D&}"Tom and Bob the Quail"{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.26,0:00:24.11,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:20260,24110}Say, father, before we go, let's stop\Nand give our farewells to Johnny and Polly!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.11,0:00:27.26,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:24110,27260}Yeah, let's do that. Those two really did\Ntreat us with kindness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.91,0:00:35.27,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:33910,35270}Good morning, Johnny, Polly!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:51.33,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:47440,51330}- Well, Mr. Condor!\N-You're all together! Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.51,0:00:55.69,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:51510,55690}No, we're moving to the South country,\Nso we stopped by to extend our farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.21,0:00:57.44,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:56210,57440}Thanks for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.83,0:00:59.73,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:57830,59730}Oh, you're really going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.73,0:01:02.29,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:59730,62290}How disappointing! Say, instead\Nof going to the South country,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.48,0:01:04.34,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:62480,64340}can't you live here throughout the year?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.40,0:01:06.88,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:65400,66880}Don't you be silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.42,0:01:10.05,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:67420,70050}For us the cold is just not\Nfor our nature, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.13,0:01:13.09,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:70130,73090}Just as you good people pass\Nthe winter in your burrows,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.09,0:01:16.19,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:73090,76190}we too shall be warm in our special place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.41,0:01:20.25,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:76410,80250}Is that so? Recently the swallows moved out,\Nyesterday, the cuckoo bird...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.51,0:01:24.25,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:80510,84250}With everyone leaving, the Green Forest\Nbecomes a very lonely place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.62,0:01:28.45,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:84620,88450}But of course, that doesn't mean that\Nwe'll never meet again, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.56,0:01:31.64,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:88560,91640}Of course, we'll surely be back again,\Nnext spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.43,0:01:32.96,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:92430,92960}Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.58,0:01:34.66,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:93580,94660}Listen, Polly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.96,0:01:37.87,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:94960,97870}Let's go see the condor family off\Nto the end of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.91,0:01:39.13,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:97910,99130}- OK?\N- OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.13,0:01:40.24,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:99130,100240}Well, stay healthy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.15,0:02:05.75,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:122150,125750}Listen, both of you, you have gone\Nfar enough, do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.75,0:02:07.18,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:125750,127180}Our best regards to everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.29,0:02:09.67,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:127290,129670}We'll be waiting with pleasure\Nto meet you next spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.68,0:02:11.10,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:129680,131100}- Goodbye, goodbye!\N- Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.19,0:02:12.62,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:131190,132620}Thank you, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.62,0:02:13.86,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:132620,133860}- Stay healthy!\N- Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.13,0:02:27.92,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:147130,147920}Hi, Bob!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.49,0:02:31.87,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:148490,151870}Surely you're not gonna say you're moving\Nto the South country, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.39,0:02:34.99,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:153390,154990}We aren't that sensitive to cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.74,0:02:38.32,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:155740,158320}We're just go to Mr Brown's field\Nto gather some wheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:41.48,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:158470,161480}Oh, is that it?\NMy, that's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.24,0:02:46.67,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:165240,166670}Well, children, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.51,0:03:07.42,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:183510,187420}- Now, eat all you want!\N- But don't wander off too far, little children!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.88,0:03:12.46,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:189880,192460}{\i1}Since it's already autumn,\Nharvesting is over.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.94,0:03:15.12,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:192940,195120}{\i1}The Bob's family has throughout the summer{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.54,0:03:17.67,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:195540,197670}{\i1}foraged all over Mr. Brown's field.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.26,0:03:21.00,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:198260,201000}{\i1}Bob and his family have eaten up\Nall kinds of wheat seeds,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:24.27,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:201000,204270}{\i1}and naturally, their favorites, those green\Nworms that could've destroyed the crops.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.54,0:03:27.46,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:204540,207460}{\i1}Now they're munching on white butterflies\Nthat lay their eggs on cabbages.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.24,0:03:30.06,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:208240,210060}{\i1}And these eggs, if left alone,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.07,0:03:33.11,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:210070,213110}{\i1}will develop into caterpillars,\Nwhich could destroy the cabbages.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.71,0:03:35.74,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:213710,215740}{\i1}In the wheat field, there are other insects{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.74,0:03:38.32,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:215740,218320}{\i1}which suck the fluid from the wheat stock,\Nkilling it.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.36,0:03:40.62,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:218360,220620}{\i1}Bob and his family ate these pests too.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.05,0:03:53.09,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:232050,233090}Is everyone alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.51,0:03:57.93,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:236510,237930}Two, three, four...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.57,0:03:59.96,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:238570,239960}Dear, Mike is missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.56,0:04:02.38,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:241560,242380}What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.86,0:04:06.68,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:243860,246680}What shall we do?\NWait, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.87,0:04:09.26,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:247870,249260}To look for Mike in the wheat field!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.75,0:04:11.30,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:249750,251300}Don't be foolish, darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.72,0:04:15.27,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:251720,255270}- If you go now, you'll just be shot!\N- But Mike has disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.55,0:04:16.78,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:255550,256780}Just take it easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.59,0:04:57.16,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:294590,297160}Oh, what happened?\NAh! Oh, the blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.57,0:05:14.17,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:313570,314170}Let's run!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:23.85,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:322380,323850}Polly, hide in here, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.41,0:05:28.47,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:327410,328470}Johnny, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.14,0:06:07.09,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:364140,367090}Is the scent gone? Can't be helped.\NLet's give up and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:16.37,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:372500,376370}- It looks like they're finally gone.\N- Yeah, but they sure do some cruel things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.55,0:06:23.44,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:380550,383440}Better hurry and tell Bob,\Nthey surely must be worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.26,0:06:29.55,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:386260,389550}That's true. I'll hurry and go tell them.\NSo you look after Mike, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.47,0:06:30.97,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:390470,390970}But hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:53.34,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:411260,413340}Oh! What's this crying...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.89,0:06:56.06,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:413890,416060}You're a boy, aren't you... huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.67,0:06:59.15,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:416670,419150}Such a small thing, you can bare it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.68,0:07:04.79,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:422680,424790}Oh, that's a good boy, Mike!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.19,0:07:11.87,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:428190,431870}Sure is late!\NYou can stay here by yourself, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.53,0:07:15.66,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:433530,435660}Now-now, you needn't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.82,0:07:19.96,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:435820,439960}I'm just going to go and find your parents, OK?\NNow, don't wander off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.17,0:07:22.06,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:440170,442060}Stay quietly here, understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.24,0:07:36.55,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:455240,456550}Hey, Mikey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.96,0:07:39.62,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:456960,459620}He hurt his wing and can't fly,\Nbut... he's alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:56.25,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:473520,476250}Uh, well, hello there, little quail!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.37,0:07:59.65,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:476370,479650}You must be lonely there all by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.02,0:08:02.27,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:480020,482270}Well, shall I play with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:26.38,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:503620,506380}- Ah, Johnny! Oh!\N- Polly, did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.79,0:08:29.56,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:506790,509560}Well, you were so late,\Nthat I came to see what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.59,0:08:32.11,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:509590,512110}Now hurry!\NMikey is waiting eagerly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.21,0:08:38.44,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:516210,518440}Mike, your mother and father are here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.05,0:08:44.23,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:523050,524230}Where is Mike?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.02,0:08:49.13,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:525020,529130}That's strange, I told him to stay here\Nand not go out anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.56,0:08:51.97,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:530560,531970}Mike! Mikey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.26,0:10:07.86,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:607260,607860}Sammy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.40,0:10:11.97,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:609400,611970}Say, what are you searching for,\Nfor what, tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.28,0:10:14.89,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:612280,614890}Sammy!\NHave you seen Mike around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.43,0:10:16.85,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:615430,616850}Mike?\NYeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.51,0:10:19.01,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:617510,619010}Mike, you say? Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.89,0:10:20.70,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:619890,620700}You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.23,0:10:26.50,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:622230,626500}In other words, I know, he's one of the five kids\Nof Bob, isn't that right, Johnny?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:28.54,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:627310,628540}That's right, that's Mike.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.19,0:10:32.85,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:629190,632850}Then, just a while ago, Tom caught him\Nand took him to his house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.24,0:10:34.38,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:633240,634380}Tom did, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.00,0:10:38.95,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:635000,638950}Yeah...! From all appearances, it looked like\Nhe would be eaten, I'm sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.44,0:10:43.38,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:642440,643380}Eaten? Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.80,0:10:51.06,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:646800,651060}- Johnny, where are you going?\N- I'm going to Mr. Brown's house, Polly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.95,0:10:57.21,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:655950,657210}{\i1}Johnny meant business.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.45,0:11:02.01,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:657450,662010}{\i1}If necessary, he'd bite Tom's hand, whatever\Nhe had to do, he was going to help Mike escape.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.06,0:11:39.92,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:697060,699920}Hi, young man, that quail is the one\Nthat I shot not too long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.20,0:11:41.22,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:700200,701220}How about returning it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.83,0:11:44.64,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:702830,704640}No, sir... I won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.40,0:11:48.03,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:705400,708030}You, sir... you may have shot him,\Nbut he's not yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.43,0:11:51.11,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:708430,711110}I found him at our field, so he's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.58,0:11:53.45,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:712580,713450}I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:55.37,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:713840,715370}If I say no, it's no!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:59.81,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:715610,719810}Furthermore, don't shoot guns in our field.\NThe quails in our field work all summer in our behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.81,0:12:02.83,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:719810,722830}Just because harvest time is over,\Nit's no reason for you to shoot them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.17,0:12:06.43,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:724170,726430}But the law permits the shooting of birds!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.03,0:12:09.63,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:727030,729630}In my heart, that's a mistake!\NSuch laws are wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.63,0:12:12.33,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:729630,732330}Oh, you shouldn't get so mad\Nover a thing like a meaningless bird,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.33,0:12:14.19,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:732330,734190}these things were born to be shot by men.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:15.47,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:734220,735470}Oh, no, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.32,0:12:19.50,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:736320,739500}You're mistaken!\NBirds, men, they're all the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.64,0:12:21.84,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:739640,741840}{\i1}Just like us, they become happy or sad.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.13,0:12:24.48,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:742130,744480}Look, sir, when you come near,\Nhow frightened he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.48,0:12:27.04,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:744480,747040}Please, leave, and never again\Nshoot a gun in our field!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.82,0:12:35.38,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:753820,755380}You're safe now, little bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.42,0:12:38.66,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757420,758660}You just take it easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.64,0:12:43.57,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:761640,763570}We're gonna go for just a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.48,0:12:48.49,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:766480,768490}Come on, let's go, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.51,0:12:51.31,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769510,771310}Mrs. Bob has a glutton for punishment!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.70,0:12:53.41,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771700,773410}She doesn't have to see him everyday!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.68,0:12:56.02,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:773680,776020}But still I am apprehensive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.91,0:13:09.23,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:786910,789230}Johnny! Oh, terrible, something terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.67,0:13:11.89,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:789670,791890}Polly, what are you so excited about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.02,0:13:15.87,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:792020,795870}Just now I met Bob and he said\NMike can't be seen anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.21,0:13:17.00,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:796210,797000}Mike can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:21.46,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:797540,801460}Yes, and he said he thinks\Nmaybe Tom has killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.58,0:13:25.30,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:802580,805300}Hardly, Tom isn't the type to do such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.43,0:13:28.28,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:805430,808280}I told him that too, but then he said,\N"If we look for him,"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.56,0:13:30.34,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:808560,810340}"then we should be able to find him"!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.75,0:13:35.47,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:812750,815470}I wonder if he really has been killed,\Nlike Bob says.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.47,0:13:37.21,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:815470,817210}If so, it's my fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.21,0:13:39.76,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:817210,819760}Polly, it's much to soon to decide\Nthat he's been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.76,0:13:43.24,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:819760,823240}Just to be sure, let's go see one more time.\NLet's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.66,0:14:22.35,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:860660,862350}Polly, run away, run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:55.98,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:892820,895980}- What's so funny?\N- About Mike being in such a place!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.30,0:14:58.13,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:896300,898130}Mike, you said, where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.41,0:15:01.08,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:899410,901080}Look, is he over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.55,0:15:04.60,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:901550,904600}No wonder we couldn't find him\Nwith all that searching we've been doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.88,0:15:15.00,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:910880,915000}{\i1}Up to now, Mike has lived all his life\Nin the wide forest and meadow.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.69,0:15:19.86,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:915690,919860}{\i1}Now, Tom realized that he'd be\Ncramped and miserable in such a small box.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.42,0:15:22.31,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:920420,922310}{\i1}So, he moved him to the shed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.27,0:15:47.32,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:946270,947320}Then Mike is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.21,0:15:50.96,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:949210,950960}- Then he's really alright?\N- Alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.12,0:15:54.38,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:951120,954380}Yes, he is living in good health\Nin Mr. Brown's chicken shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.52,0:15:55.48,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:954520,955480}So, be at ease!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.62,0:15:57.48,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:955620,957480}Mother, don't you think that's swell?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.48,0:16:00.79,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:957480,960790}Y-yes... but a chicken shed, what kind a place is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.17,0:16:01.98,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:961170,961980}A chicken shed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.21,0:16:05.59,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:962210,965590}Oh, a place where they put those, you know,\Nbirds that cockle-doodle-do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.07,0:16:08.88,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:966070,968880}But what is that child doing in such a place?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.20,0:16:10.63,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:969200,970630}He's locked in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.02,0:16:14.07,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:971020,974070}My, he's suffering such a predicament,\Nhow can I not worry?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.18,0:16:16.40,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:974180,976400}But Mike has been shot,\Nso he can not fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.40,0:16:18.77,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:976400,978770}I think he would not have been able\Nto continue living
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:21.05,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:979040,981050}if he had not been here, Mrs. Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.34,0:16:25.70,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:981340,985700}That's right. Sooner or later I think\Nhe would be caught by Reddy or a hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.86,0:16:29.60,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:985860,989600}But if he stays there, Reddy won't be able\Nto do a thing, uh-uh!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.87,0:16:33.31,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:990870,993310}Mother, it's just like\Nwhat Johnny has been saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.66,0:16:35.71,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:993660,995710}Mike is in a place like a big bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.84,0:16:39.02,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:995840,999020}and Mike cannot leave,\Nbut neither can Reddy nor a hawk enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.29,0:16:42.73,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:999290,1002730}A more safer place I don't think\Ncan be be found anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.52,0:16:47.51,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1003520,1007510}Naturally, that's not all.\NTom is really friendly with Mike.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.51,0:16:47.95,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1007510,1007950}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:52.30,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1008270,1012300}From the distance, we saw Mike leap\Non Tom's hand and eat some food.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.46,0:16:54.86,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1012460,1014860}I'm convinced Tom is really our friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.99,0:17:29.90,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1047990,1049900}Mrs. Bob, are you still worried after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.49,0:17:31.92,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1050490,1051920}Mother, let's just trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.08,0:17:35.76,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1052080,1055760}Tom is a good boy, and I'm sure\Nthat just as soon as the wing heals,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.94,0:17:38.55,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1055940,1058550}he'll let our boy come home,\NI'm sure of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.35,0:17:48.78,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1065350,1068780}{\i1}From that moment on,\NBob and Mrs. Bob went every day{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.98,0:17:51.26,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1068980,1071260}{\i1}to see how their little Mike was getting along.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.26,0:17:59.00,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1075260,1079000}{\i1}And every day, Mike's wound appeared\Nto be getting better and beter.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.97,0:18:09.08,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1083970,1089080}{\i1}And then, one fine day, as Mr. and Mrs. Bob\Ncame flying over as usual...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.05,0:18:20.92,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1100050,1100920}- Mikey!\N- Mikey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.90,0:18:40.22,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1117900,1120220}- Mike, you can fly!\N- Good boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:44.46,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1120220,1124460}Isn't it wonderful, my wing? Isn't it?\NTom cured it for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:11.97,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148620,1151970}Oh, it must be that Mike has come home!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.97,0:19:14.78,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151970,1154780}Uh-uh, usually he doesn't whistle at this time,\Nthat must be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.87,0:19:16.38,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1154870,1156380}Sounds real happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.19,0:20:19.19,fables default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1215190,1219190}{\c&HFFFFFF&}Subtitle: {\c&H1BEAED&}South Wind Subs
